== Print resources ==
=== Multi-volume document compilations ===
* ''Early Mormon Documents'' (1996–2003) — 5 volumes; [[Dan Vogel]], editor <small>(Signature Books)</small>
* ''[[History of the Church (Joseph Smith)|History of the Church]]'' (1902–1912) — 7 volumes; [[B.H. Roberts]], editor <small>(LDS Church affiliated)</small><ref>The ''[[History of the Church (Joseph Smith)|History of the Church]]'', also known as the ''Documentary History of the Church'', was based on the multi-volume ''Manuscript History of the Church'' and decades of additional work of the Church Historian's Office.</ref>
* ''[[The Joseph Smith Papers]]'' (2008–ongoing) — 15 out of about two dozen projected volumes, as of 2017 <small>(jointly affiliated: LDS Church  and US [[National Historical Publications and Records Commission]])</small>
* ''[https://history.lds.org/article/journal_history_guide?lang=eng Journal History of the Church]'' (1906–2008) — Over 1,200 volumes, compiled by the LDS Church as a massive daily record<ref>{{cite journal | author=Gary James Bergera | title="The Commencement of Great Things": The Origins, Scope, and Achievement of the Journal History of the Church | journal=[[Mormon Historical Studies]] | date=Spring 2003 | volume=4 | issue=1 | page=23 | url=http://mormonhistoricsites.org/mormon-historical-studies-spring-2003-vol-4-no-1/ | accessdate=2015-01-07}}</ref>
* ''[[Journal of Discourses]]'' (1854–1886) — 26 volumes of sermons by LDS Church leaders <small>(LDS Church affiliated; non-"canonical")</small>
* Significant Mormon Diaries series (1987–2013) — 13 volumes <small>(Signature Books)</small><ref>{{cite web | title=Cowboy Apostle | date=December 2013 | work=Signature Books | url=http://www.signaturebooks.com/product/cowboy-apostle// | accessdate=2018-01-29}}</ref>

